    entry_requirements = '<div class="collapse assumed-knowledge-collapse px-5 py-3 show" id="accordion-850021039578800"> <div class="parsys"> <div class="course-details section"> <div class="introduction"> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learn to teach English and other Languages</p> <div> With no previous teaching qualification or experience required, the Graduate Certificate in Teaching English to Speakers of Other Languages (TESOL) and Foreign Language Teaching (FLT) will prepare you for a rewarding career teaching language, in Australia and overseas. You will study the methodology behind teaching as well as linguistics for language teachers, and experience practical hands-on learning. </div> <div> This flexible course can be studied either full-time in one semester (4-months) or part-time in one year. Learning is 100% online meaning you can study at your own pace and when it suits you. </div> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Study a Graduate Certificate in TESOL &amp; FLT at UC and you will:</p> <ul> <li>gain advanced knowledge and skills for professional practice in language teaching and learning</li> <li>develop your understanding of a range of cultural, social and religious backgrounds </li> <li>gain an internationally recognised qualification you can use anywhere in the world</li> <li>integrate theory and practice to build your knowledge in teaching linguistics and,</li> <li>explore language teaching methodology and general pedagogy. </li> </ul> <p>Work Integrated Learning (WIL)<br/> WIL is an integral part of the UC journey and all students are encouraged to actively attend and participate in relevant placements, workshops, conferences and events where they will have the opportunity to engage with both internal and external stakeholders at all levels.</p> <p>This approach provides students with an invaluable opportunity to meet and build strong networking relationships with industry professionals, greatly enhancing their employability upon graduation. On completion of this course, students are expected to have accumulated at least 20 hours of work-integrated learning.</p> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Career opportunities</p> <ul> <li>Teaching English to migrants and refugees </li> <li>Teaching a foreign language to speakers of English </li> <li>Working in community language schools </li> <li>Teaching languages in schools</li> <li>Teaching English as an additional language or dialect for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples</li> </ul> <p style="font-weight: bold;">Course specific information</p> <div> Graduate and be ready to teach English to speakers of other languages. With a Graduate Certificate in TESOL/FLT you will be ready to walk straight into teaching. </div> <div> Looking to upgrade your qualification? This course serves as a pathway into the Graduate Diploma and Master in Teaching English as a Second Language (TESOL) and Foreign Language Teaching (FLT). </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>',
